OL,4,Cfor patient to have what she wanted'
OL,6,FPaterson said he could not remember if
OL,7,Fhe knew at that point whether he was
OL,8,Fbeing investigated, but said the MDT
OL,9,Fwas "a bit dysfunctional", claiming
OL,10,Fhis "whistleblowing accusations"
OL,11,Fagainst another doctor "had become
OL,12,Fpublic knowledge".
OL,14,FHe told the inquest: "I felt that a
OL,15,Flot of decision making in the MDT was
OL,16,Ffactional rather than clinical.
OL,18,F"This was one of those cases where
OL,19,Fwhatever I said was going to be
OL,20,Fdisagreed with, not purely on clinical
OL,21,Fgrounds."
