OL,4,Cfor patient to have what she wanted'
OL,6,FAsked about the 2005 mastectomy,
OL,7,FPaterson said he had intended to
OL,8,Fremove all the breast tissue he could,
OL,9,Fand it was not his intention to leave
OL,10,Fany.
OL,12,FHe was questioned about medical
OL,13,Frecords showing the amount of tissue
OL,14,Fremoved during the procedure had
OL,15,Fweighed 209 grams.
OL,17,FAsked by Mr Jones whether he
OL,18,Fconsidered that was "light for someone
OL,19,Fwith 34B cup breasts", Paterson said:
OL,20,F"No, not really. The weight is the
OL,21,Fweight.
