OL,6,FMr Jones asked Paterson about another
OL,7,Fdocument showing Mrs Baker's tumour
OL,8,Fwent right to the excision margin `
OL,9,Fthe edge of tissue removed during the
OL,10,Fprocedure, saying: "Is this something
OL,11,Fthe patient should know, that the
OL,12,Ftumour has not been completely
OL,13,Fremoved?"
OL,15,FPaterson said: "You are speculating
OL,16,Fthat the tumour has not been
OL,17,Fcompletely removed and I think it was."
OL,19,FHe told the inquest Mrs Baker did not
OL,20,Frelapse at the mastectomy site.
